## 🔧 Common Commands

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone <repo_url>

# Create branch
git checkout -b feature-name

# Stage changes
git add .

# Commit changes
git commit -m "message"

# Push to remote
git push origin branch_name

# Pull latest changes
git pull origin main

# Fetch without merging
git fetch origin

# Delete local branch
git branch -d branch_name

# Delete remote branch
git push origin --delete branch_name
```

---

## ⚠️ Important Concepts

* **origin** → default remote repository
* **upstream** → original repo (in fork workflow)
* **protected branch** → restricted branch (no direct push)
* **merge conflict** → same code modified in multiple places

